WEBVTT

0
00:00:03.329 --> 00:00:06.409
The transition to the open rack wide introduces

1
00:00:06.409 --> 00:00:10.470
a massive new logistical challenge for facility operators.

2
00:00:11.399 --> 00:00:17.899
A fully populated ORW AI rack can easily weigh up to 3500 kg.

3
00:00:19.159 --> 00:00:23.610
At this extreme scale and beyond across multiple such racks,

4
00:00:23.690 --> 00:00:26.850
we are no longer just managing IT gear.

5
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.379
We are managing heavy industry.

6
00:00:31.510 --> 00:00:31.520
Because

7
00:00:31.950 --> 00:00:33.430
of this immense weight,

8
00:00:33.830 --> 00:00:37.689
standard rolling casters are no longer a safe or viable option.

9
00:00:39.189 --> 00:00:43.000
The ORW frame eliminates casters entirely.

10
00:00:43.389 --> 00:00:45.990
The rack is designed to sit directly on

11
00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:50.060
structural platforms using dedicated pallet mounting brackets.

12
00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:55.270
This guarantees maximum stability and prevents catastrophic floor damage.

13
00:00:55.790 --> 00:01:01.590
Transporting a 3500 kg machine requires precision mechanization.

14
00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:05.120
The ORW base provides the specific

15
00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:08.860
clearances required for automated rack transport carts

16
00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:10.160
to safely lift,

17
00:01:10.470 --> 00:01:11.120
maneuver,

18
00:01:11.239 --> 00:01:13.599
and deploy the payload down the aisle.

19
00:01:14.639 --> 00:01:15.480
Once secured,

20
00:01:15.599 --> 00:01:19.760
operators must manage the massive data requirements of the AI cluster.

21
00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:26.470
The ORW frame incorporates spacious top and rear cable channels.

22
00:01:27.069 --> 00:01:29.309
These dedicated routing paths keep

23
00:01:29.309 --> 00:01:32.089
massive bundles of optical interconnects completely

24
00:01:32.089 --> 00:01:36.129
secure and safely out of the primary thermal exhaust path.

25
00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:41.209
By standardizing these transport and cabling interfaces,

26
00:01:41.419 --> 00:01:46.599
OCP ensures that deploying massive infrastructure remains safe,

27
00:01:47.059 --> 00:01:50.519
but standards like this are a continuous work in progress.

28
00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:54.900
Because there is still room for defining new standards

29
00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:57.849
for the next generation of heavy wide racks.

30
00:01:58.879 --> 00:02:00.760
We actively invite the community to

31
00:02:00.760 --> 00:02:03.940
participate in generating any missing specifications.

32
00:02:05.620 --> 00:02:10.110
Join the work group today to help shape the future of high density deployment.